# SIDE QUEST — "The Mournlight"  (requires sq.carry_the_mournlight)
# You carry the Mournlight — ten thousand forbidden mournings made into light, the golden-path key, that
# can only be borne by a grief one was never allowed to feel. It is not a weapon and not a lamp. It is an
# indictment that shines. This quest is the moment you decide what the carried grief is FOR.
class: MournlightSideQuestContent

# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# "The Mournlight" — what the carried grief of ten thousand forbidden mournings is for, at the end.
# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
conversation: sq.mournlight.thread | The Mournlight
node: 0 | The Mournlight
  *(It rests in your keeping where no lamp could — the Mournlight, ten thousand forbidden mournings distilled into a radiance that weeps without water, the grief of every soul ever told it had no right to grieve a Faithless dead. It chose you because you carry a grief you were never allowed to feel, and only that grief can bear it. As you near the Court, it brightens — not with welcome, but with *recognition*, the way grief recognizes the place where the wrong that made it was done. It is not asking to be set down. It is asking what it is *for.*)*
  enter: SET sq.mournlight_thread_begun
  auto: 1
node: 1 | The Mournlight
  *(The light gathers into the layered voice you first heard — the chord of a thousand denied sorrows — quieter now, closer, urgent.)* We are near the place. *(the radiance trembles.)* The Court. Where the *forbidding* was *decided* — where the *doctrine* was written that said *"the Faithless are owed no grief,"* that turned ten thousand years of *mothers* and *widows* and *friends* into people *forbidden* to *mourn* their own *dead.* *(the light intensifies.)* I am *made* of their *defiance.* Every tear they *shed anyway*, every grief they *kept* though they were *told* they had *no right* — *distilled*, *gathered*, made into the *one* thing the powers of the dead *cannot* answer: not an *argument* that *grief* is *owed*, but *grief itself*, *happening*, *visible*, *undeniable.* *(the voice fills with terrible purpose.)* You have *carried* me here on the *one* grief you were *never allowed to feel* — the *quiet* one, the *forbidden* one, the loss the *world* told you *not* to mourn. *(the radiance turns to you.)* So now I ask what I have *waited* ten thousand years to ask the *one* who could *carry* me: *what am I for?* Am I a *light* you *shine*? A *weight* you *set down*? A *grief* you *add* to? *Decide*, Returned. We are *at* the *threshold*, and a *grief* this *old* should not arrive *purposeless.*
  * [INSIGHT 18] "You're not a lamp and you're not a weapon. You're an *exhibit.* The Court has answers for arguments — doctrine, precedent, ten thousand years of 'they chose the nothing.' But you're not an argument. You're the *grief they forbade*, made visible, happening in front of them. You can't refute a tear. You're the one indictment that wins by *shining.*" -> indict ?? close_light
  * "The golden road is dark — Jergal said so, the dim keyhole beside the bright crown. A grief made of light is the one thing that can *light* it. Be the lantern for the road the crown's glare hides. Let the mourning of ten thousand forbidden mourners show me the way the powers don't want me to find." -> golden_road
  * "I won't just shine you at them. I'll add my own. The grief I was never allowed to feel — the quiet one that let me carry you — I'll let it *into* you, here, at the threshold, so that when you shine, mine shines too, and the indictment includes the one mourner who finally stopped being forbidden." -> add_grief | fx SET sq.mournlight_grief_added
  * "Tell me whose grief you are. Not 'ten thousand mournings' — one of them. One specific mother, one widow, one friend forbidden to weep. Let me carry a *face*, not a number, to the Court. A grief with a name behind it shines truer than a grief that's only vast." -> whose | fx appr.naeve +2
node: indict | The Mournlight
  *(The radiance *surges*, the chord ringing with something fierce and vindicated.)* An *exhibit.* *(the light blazes.)* Not an *argument.* *(the voice fills.)* You *understand* what I *am* — what *Naeve's* indictment is, what the *Complaint's* grievances are, what the *whole* road has been *gathering*: not *cases* the powers can *win*, but *evidence* they *cannot answer.* *(the radiance intensifies toward the Court.)* And I am the *purest* of them — because a *ledger* they can *dispute*, a *testimony* they can *discredit*, a *name* they can *deny* — but a *grief*, *shining*, *happening*, *visible* — *(fierce.)* — *that* they can only *forbid*, and I *am* the grief they *already* *forbade* and that *fell* *anyway.* *(the voice rings.)* When you *shine* me at the *Court*, the powers will *say* — as they have *always* said — *"the Faithless are owed no mourning."* And I will *answer*, not in *words*, but in *light*: *ten thousand mournings, happening, in front of them, in defiance of the very doctrine they're reciting.* *(the radiance soars.)* You *cannot* out-argue a *tear.* You can only *command* it *not* to *fall* — and I am *every* tear they *commanded* not to fall, *falling.* *(the light turns to you.)* *Shine* me, Returned. At the *one* court that *forbade* the *grief* I'm *made* of. Let them *try* to *rule* that *ten thousand years* of *mourning* *isn't* *happening* while it *blazes* in their *own* *chamber.* *That* is what I'm *for.* I have *always* been *for* this. I only needed *hands* that *grieved* in the *forbidden* way to *carry* me to the *room* where the *forbidding* *lives.*
  enter: SET sq.mournlight_shone_at_court, SET act5.the_great_objection, SET act2.golden_path_key, SET act1.mercy_remembered, appr.ilfaeril +5
  auto: 2
node: golden_road | The Mournlight
  *(The radiance shifts — from the fierce edge of indictment to something steadier, a lantern-warmth.)* The golden road. *(the chord softens.)* The *dim* keyhole. *(the light gathers.)* Jergal told you *true* — the *crown* is *bright*, *certain*, *glaring*, and its *glare* is *exactly* what *hides* the *other* road, the *golden* one, the *dim* path to *the fall, the ending, the letting-go.* *(the radiance warms.)* And a *grief made of light* — *(the voice fills with purpose)* — I am the *one* light that does *not* *glare.* I do not *dazzle.* I *weep.* I *shine* the way *grief* shines — *soft*, *true*, *showing* what the *bright* things *hide.* *(the light steadies into a lantern.)* So let me be the *lamp* for the road the *crown's* glare *conceals.* When you reach the *threshold* and the *crown* *blazes* its *certainty* — *"wear me, rule them, do it kinder"* — and the *golden* road *dims* to *nothing* beside it — *(the radiance brightens, gentle and sure)* — *look* to *me.* I am *grief*, and *grief* knows the way to *the ending*, because *grief* is what you *feel* at an *ending*, and a *thing* made of *ten thousand mournings* can *only* point *one* way: *toward* the *fall*, the *rest*, the *letting-go* the *crown* *forbids.* *(the voice softens.)* The *crown* lights the road to *more keeping.* I light the road to *release.* *Carry* me *down* the *dim* path, Returned — let the *mourning* of ten thousand *forbidden* mourners *show* you the way the *powers* *built* their *glare* to *hide.* *Grief* is the *lantern* for the *golden* road. It *always* was.
  enter: SET sq.mournlight_lights_golden_road, SET act5.golden_road_known, SET act2.golden_path_key, SET act3.break_the_crown_known, appr.naeve +5
  auto: 2
node: add_grief | The Mournlight
  *(The radiance stills, and then — slowly, with a reverence that quiets the whole chord — it *opens* to you, the way a held hand opens.)* Add your own. *(the voice is hushed.)* The grief you were *never allowed* to feel — the *quiet* one — the loss the *world* told you *not* to *mourn.* *(the light reaches toward you.)* I have *carried* ten thousand mournings, and *every* one was a grief *forbidden* — a *mother* told *"do not weep, he chose it,"* a *widow* told *"he is nothing, mourn him not."* *(the radiance gentles.)* And *yours* — the one that let you *bear* me, the one *grief* you *match* — has been *forbidden* too, all this time, *carried* *small* and *silent* because the *world* gave it *no* *place* to *land.* *(the voice fills.)* So *land* it. *Here.* In *me.* Let your *forbidden* grief *join* the *ten thousand*, and when I *shine*, you *shine* *too* — not as the *carrier* of *others'* mourning, but as *one* of the *mourners*, *finally*, your *quiet* loss made *part* of the *indictment*, your *forbidden* tear *falling* with *all* the *rest.* *(the radiance brightens, and you feel it — your grief, the one you were never allowed, *received* at last, *welcomed*, made *part* of something *vast* and *true*.)* You have *carried* the *grief* of *ten thousand* *strangers* to the *Court.* *Carry* your *own* with them. The *forbidding* ends for *you*, too, here — the *one* mourner who *finally* *stopped* being *forbidden* is *you*, Returned. *Add* your *grief.* *Let* it *shine.* You have been *holding* it *alone* and *silent* long enough.
  enter: SET sq.mournlight_grief_added, SET act5.the_great_objection, SET act2.golden_path_key, SET act1.mercy_remembered, appr.naeve +6
  auto: 2
node: whose | The Mournlight
  *(The radiance softens, and from the vast layered chord, a single thread rises — one voice, lifted clear of the ten thousand.)* Whose grief. *(the chord stills around the one voice.)* ...Let me *give* you *one.* *(the single voice, a woman's, grief-worn and specific.)* Her name was *Aline.* Her *son* — *Joss*, a *fisher*, *nineteen* — *doubted* the *sea-gods* the *winter* the *catch* failed and the *village* starved, said *"if they're gods, let them feed us,"* and *died* that *spring* of a *fever*, and the *priest* *walled* him *Faithless*, and told *Aline*, at the *graveside* that *wasn't* a *grave*, *"do not mourn him; he chose the nothing; your tears are a* sin."* *(the voice trembles.)* And *Aline* — she *obeyed.* For *thirty* *years.* *Swallowed* it. *Never* *wept* for *Joss*, *never* *said* his *name*, *believed* she had *no right*, until she *died* herself, *still* *holding* the *forbidden* grief, *unshed*, *thirty* years *old.* *(the radiance fills.)* *That* grief — *Aline's* *thirty* *unshed* *years* for *Joss* the *doubting* *fisher* — is *in* me. *One* of *ten thousand.* But *now* you *carry* a *face*, a *name*, a *son*, a *mother* who *obeyed* the *forbidding* till it *killed* her *holding* it. *(the voice fills with purpose.)* *Carry* *Aline* to the *Court.* And when the *powers* say *"the Faithless are owed no mourning,"* you *shine*, and you *say*: *"Then answer to Aline, who obeyed you for thirty years, and died still grieving the son you told her was nothing. Was her grief a sin? Look at it. It's shining. Rule that it isn't happening."* *(the radiance soars.)* A grief with a *face* shines *truer* than a grief that's only *vast.* Carry *Aline.* Carry *Joss.* Let them be the *face* of the *ten thousand.*
  enter: SET sq.mournlight_carries_aline, SET act5.the_great_objection, SET act2.golden_path_key, SET act1.mercy_remembered, appr.naeve +5
  auto: 2
node: 2 | The Mournlight
  *(The Mournlight blazes soft and weeping in your keeping — ten thousand forbidden mournings made into the one light the powers of the dead cannot answer, carried here on the single grief you were never allowed to feel — and it waits, at the threshold of the Court, to learn what the carried sorrow will become.)*
  * "Shine it at the Court — the indictment that wins by being seen. And carry it down the golden road after, because a grief made of light is both the exhibit that damns the keeping and the lantern that finds the release. Let the mourning do both: condemn the Wall, and light the way to its ending." -> both | fx SET sq.mournlight_shone_at_court, SET sq.mournlight_lights_golden_road, SET act5.golden_road_known, appr.ilfaeril +4
  * "Add my own grief to it first, then shine it. Let the ten thousand forbidden mournings include, at last, the one I was never allowed to feel — so the indictment is carried not by a witness to grief but by a mourner who finally joined it. The forbidding ends for me in the same blaze that ends it for them." -> add_then_shine | fx SET sq.mournlight_grief_added, SET sq.mournlight_shone_at_court, appr.naeve +4
  * "Don't aim it at the powers at all. Aim it at the *dead* — shine it on the Faithless themselves, in the Wall, so that every walled soul about to be freed knows, in the moment of release, that they *were* mourned, by someone, somewhere, in defiance of every order not to. Let the last thing the kept feel be that they were grieved." -> shine_on_the_dead | fx SET sq.mournlight_shone_on_the_dead, appr.naeve +4
node: both | The Mournlight
  *(The radiance surges, fierce and warm at once, the indictment and the lantern in a single light.)* Both. *(the chord rings.)* *Condemn* the *keeping* — and *light* the *release.* *(the light blazes.)* Yes. That is what a *grief made of light* is *for*, at the *end* — not *one* thing but *the whole arc:* I *shine* at the *Court*, and the powers *cannot* *answer* the *ten thousand mournings* *happening* in their *chamber*; and *then*, when the *crown* *blazes* its *certainty* and the *golden* road *dims*, I *turn* from *indictment* to *lantern* and *light* the *dim* path the *glare* *hides.* *(the voice fills.)* *Grief* *damns* the *thing* that *caused* it — and *grief* *knows* the *way* to the *ending*, because *grief* is what you *feel* when a thing is *finally* *allowed* to *end.* *(the radiance soars.)* I will be your *exhibit* *and* your *lamp.* The *mourning* that *proves* the *Wall* a *cruelty*, and the *mourning* that *shows* the *way* to *un-make* it. *(the light turns to you, blazing and weeping both.)* *Carry* me *through* the *Court* and *down* the *golden* road, Returned. Let *ten thousand* *forbidden* mourners *condemn* the *keeping* and *light* the *release* in the *same* *breath.* That is the *most* a *grief* can *be*: not *only* a *wound*, but a *wound* that *shows* the *way* to *healing.* *Shine* me. *Both* ways. *All* the *way* to the *end.*
  enter: SET sq.mournlight_shone_at_court, SET sq.mournlight_lights_golden_road, SET act5.golden_road_known, SET act5.the_great_objection, SET act2.golden_path_key, SET act1.mercy_remembered, appr.ilfaeril +5
  auto: close
node: add_then_shine | The Mournlight
  *(The radiance opens to you first — receiving — and then, with your grief inside it, blazes brighter than it has yet.)* Yours, with the ten thousand. *(the voice is full.)* *(the light receives the quiet, forbidden grief you have carried small and silent — the loss the world told you not to mourn, the one that let you bear the Mournlight at all — and as it *lands*, *welcomed*, *part* of the *vast* chord at last, the radiance *swells*, because now it is *complete*: ten thousand *and one* forbidden mournings, and the *one* is *yours*, *finally* *unforbidden.*)* *(the chord rings with your voice in it now.)* And *now* — *now* I *shine.* *(the light blazes at the Court.)* Not carried by a *witness* to grief, but by a *mourner* who *joined* it — and when the powers *say* *"the Faithless are owed no mourning,"* you do not *argue*, you *grieve*, *openly*, *your* loss *blazing* with the *ten thousand*, and the *forbidding* that *bound* *Aline* for *thirty* years and *you* for *however* long you've *carried* your *silent* one — *(the radiance soars)* — the *forbidding* *ends*, for *all* of you, in the *same* *blaze*, in the *same* *room*, in *front* of the *ones* who *decreed* it. *(the voice fills with fierce joy.)* You stopped being *forbidden* the *moment* you *added* your *grief.* Now *show* them. *All* of you. *Mourning*, *together*, *un-forbidden*, *at last*, in the *Court* that *said* you *couldn't.* *That* is the *indictment* *and* the *liberation* in *one* light: *the mourner who finally wept.*
  enter: SET sq.mournlight_grief_added, SET sq.mournlight_shone_at_court, SET act5.the_great_objection, SET act2.golden_path_key, SET act1.mercy_remembered, appr.naeve +6
  auto: close
node: shine_on_the_dead | The Mournlight
  *(The radiance stills, and then turns — not toward the powers, but toward the Wall, toward the kept, and the chord softens into something unbearably tender.)* On the *dead.* *(the voice is hushed and full.)* Not the *powers.* The *Faithless* *themselves.* *(the light gathers, gentle.)* Oh — *that* is — in *ten thousand years* of *gathering*, *no one* has *thought* to *aim* me *there.* *(the radiance warms.)* I was *made* to *indict* — to *shine* at the *ones* who *forbade* the *grief* — and I have *always* faced *outward*, toward the *Court*, the *doctrine*, the *blame.* *(the voice trembles.)* But you would turn me *inward.* Toward the *walled.* So that *every* *Faithless* soul *about* to be *freed* — *every* *Maerys*, *every* *Halen*, *every* *Joss* the *fisher* — *feels*, in the *moment* of *release*, the *one* thing the *Wall* spent *ten thousand years* *denying* them: *that they were mourned.* *(the radiance blazes soft and weeping.)* That *somewhere*, a *mother* like *Aline* *wept* for them *thirty* *years* in *defiance* of *every* *order.* That they were *not* *nothing* — that their *passing* *broke* a *heart*, *kept* a *grief*, *mattered* to *someone* who *refused* to *stop* *mourning* them. *(the voice fills with tears.)* The *powers* don't *need* to *see* me. The *powers* *know* what they *did.* But the *dead* — the *dead* spent *ten thousand years* *believing* they *deserved* the *nothing*, *un-mourned*, *un-missed.* *(the light turns wholly toward the Wall.)* *Shine* me on *them*, Returned. Let the *last* thing the *kept* feel, in the *moment* they *fall* free, be the *ten thousand* mournings that were *forbidden* but *fell* *anyway* — *for them.* Let them *die* *knowing* they were *grieved.* *That* — *that* is a *kinder* use than *indictment.* I have *wanted*, for *ten thousand years*, to *face* the *ones* I *mourn* instead of the *ones* I *blame.* *Let* me.
  enter: SET sq.mournlight_shone_on_the_dead, SET act5.witness_then_release, SET act2.golden_path_key, SET act1.mercy_remembered, appr.naeve +6
  auto: close
node: close_light | The Mournlight
  *(The radiance dims, gentle, settling back into your keeping without judgment.)* You are not *ready* to *aim* me. *(the voice is soft.)* That is *no* failing. A *grief* this *old* should not be *spent* *uncertainly* — and *you* carry your *own*, *quiet* and *forbidden*, and *perhaps* you must *tend* *that* before you can *wield* *ten thousand* *more.* *(the light steadies.)* I will *wait.* I have *waited* ten thousand years for *hands* that could *carry* me at *all*; I can *wait* a *little* longer for *hands* that *know* what I'm *for.* *(the radiance gentles.)* *Carry* me *to* the *Court*, and when you *stand* before the *powers* and *feel* the *grief* — *yours*, and the *ten thousand* — *rise*, you will *know*, then, what I am *for.* *Grief* always *knows*, at the *end.* It only *waits* for the *moment* it *can't* be *held* *back* *anymore.* *(and the Mournlight subsides, weeping softly in your keeping, the indictment that shines, biding its time for the threshold where the carried sorrow of ten thousand forbidden mourners will, at last, refuse to stay unspent.)*
  auto: close
node: close | The Mournlight
  *(The Mournlight blazes soft and weeping in your keeping — ten thousand forbidden mournings made into the one light no power of the dead can answer, borne to the threshold of the Court on the single grief you were never allowed to feel — and whether you shone it at the powers as the indictment that wins by being seen, lit the golden road with it, added your own forbidden grief to its blaze, carried one mother's thirty unshed years as the face of the vast, or turned it inward to let the freed Faithless feel, at last, that they were mourned, you carry away the truest weapon the long road ever gave you: not a sword, not a crown, but grief — the grief they forbade and that fell anyway — made visible, undeniable, and shining, in the one room that decreed it had no right to exist.)*
